  • Classes in net.automatalib.automaton used by net.automatalib.automaton 
    Class Description
    Automaton
    Basic interface for an automaton.
    DeterministicAutomaton
    Basic interface for a deterministic automaton.
    DeterministicAutomaton.FullIntAbstraction
    Interface for full integer abstractions of a DeterministicAutomaton.
    DeterministicAutomaton.IntAbstraction
    Base interface for integer abstractions of a DeterministicAutomaton.
    DeterministicAutomaton.StateIntAbstraction
    Interface for state integer abstractions of a DeterministicAutomaton.
    FiniteAlphabetAutomaton  
    MutableAutomaton
    A mutable automaton.
    MutableDeterministic
    Interface for a mutable deterministic automaton.
    MutableDeterministic.FullIntAbstraction
    Interface for full integer abstractions of a MutableDeterministic.
    MutableDeterministic.IntAbstraction
    Base interface for integer abstractions of a MutableDeterministic.
    MutableDeterministic.StateIntAbstraction
    Interface for state integer abstractions of a MutableDeterministic.
    ShrinkableAutomaton
    A mutable automaton that also supports destructive modifications, i.e., removal of states and transitions.
    UniversalAutomaton
    A universal automaton is a generalized representation of automata, with unified access to the properties of states and transitions.
    UniversalDeterministicAutomaton
    A DeterministicAutomaton with state and transition properties.
    UniversalDeterministicAutomaton.FullIntAbstraction
    Interface for full integer abstractions of a UniversalDeterministicAutomaton.
    UniversalDeterministicAutomaton.IntAbstraction
    Base interface for integer abstractions of a UniversalDeterministicAutomaton.
    UniversalDeterministicAutomaton.StateIntAbstraction
    Interface for state integer abstractions of a UniversalDeterministicAutomaton.
